  ./search_su2_fundamental_transfer finite 8 7
  SU2_LEVEL_FUNDAMENTAL_TRANSFER levels=2..8 maximum_factors=7 cases=6434 active_wall_cases=2632 tight_wall_cases=1529 simple_current_cases=3431 minimum_wall_slack=0 required=PASS
  elapsed=2.97 maxrss=3072KB

The finite mode checks every target against
  A_(1,p) <= sum_(s in p star_k 1) A_(0,s).
It separately enforces the proved simple-current wall identity.  If one
label k is removed and A is the coefficient array of the remaining word,
then
  A'_(r,s)=A_(k-r,s)+A_(r,k-s).
Consequently
  A'_(1,k)=A_(k-1,k)+A_(1,0)
           =A_(k,k-1)+A_(0,1)=A'_(0,k-1).
Thus every plus word containing the invertible object e_k has wall
coefficient exactly zero, uniformly in k; the finite run independently
checks this identity in all 3,431 enumerated simple-current words.

The same wall equality is not restricted to one negative fundamental.
After removing one plus e_k from any odd-sign remainder, exchange
antisymmetry forces every diagonal coefficient h_(r,r) to vanish.
Reattaching e_k contributes h_(0,0)+h_(k,k)=0 at target k.  This proves the
odd-sign simple-current wall family uniformly; the enumerator above is an
independent check of its fundamental specialization.

Here
  A_(r,s)=sum_S mult_r(tensor_(i in S)V_(q_i))
                    mult_s(tensor_(i notin S)V_(q_i)).
The required one-fundamental coefficient inequality is
  A_(1,p)<=A_(0,p-1)+A_(0,p+1).
The tempting upper-branch-only strengthening A_(1,p)<=A_(0,p+1) is false.
Its smallest displayed failure is the hard Plucker word [2,2,2,2,3] at
target 2: 44>43, while the lower branch supplies 28.  Thus the p-1 term in
the deletion--contraction exact row is essential; the merged p+1 branch
cannot carry the proof by itself.
